(cpi, power_memory).explanation: CPI and memory power consumption are both outcomes of underlying architectural design decisions and workload characteristics, but CPI does not directly cause changes in memory power consumption;

(cpi, power).explanation: CPI and total power consumption are both results of processor architecture and workload characteristics, but CPI itself does not directly cause overall power consumption changes;

(cpi, power_pad).explanation: CPI and pad power consumption are independent metrics where CPI reflects instruction execution efficiency while pad power relates to I/O interface power consumption;
